        âœ… 4. Usage
        
        Now you can run pyinitpro from anywhere in your terminal:
        
        pyinitpro
        
        It will prompt you to:
        	â€¢	Create a new project or use an existing one:
        	â€¢	New project: Asks for the project name, subfolders, etc.
        	â€¢	Existing project: Asks for the path and sets up the folders.
        	â€¢	Create a Python virtual environment (optional):
        	â€¢	You can skip this with the --no-venv flag.
        	â€¢	You can specify a Python version with the --python-version flag.
        	â€¢	Add dependencies to requirements.txt:
        	â€¢	Provide a comma-separated list of dependencies via the --dependencies flag.
        	â€¢	If no dependencies are provided, a preconfigured template for requirements.txt will be created.
        	â€¢	Initialize a Git repository (optional):
        	â€¢	You can choose to initialize a Git repo by answering y when prompted.
        	â€¢	If desired, add a remote repository URL with the --git-remote flag.
        	â€¢	Interactive Setup (optional):
        	â€¢	Enable an interactive setup where you will be prompted for custom folder names by using the --interactive flag.
        
        Example usage with flags:
        
        pyinitpro --interactive --dependencies flask,requests --python-version 3.9
        
        
        
